                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#150rc">Fols. 150rc-150</locus>va: Purchase note.<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note is written both in Gǝʿǝz and in Amharic.
The note states that the church Bäʿatti Qǝddus Mikaʾel purchased the book (in the month of Mäggabit) from most probably such a Gäbrä Maryam. During the moment of the purchase witnesses from both sides, whose the names are given, were present.
Gäbrä Maryam is also mentioned in some supplication formulas within the Text (e.g., fol. 6va-c).
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Excerpts of hymns for the Good Friday (?) are written (in a faded black ink) in the upper margins, or interlineally, in fols. 83v, 89v-90r, 101v, 102r, 109r.&#xD;
- Omitted words or letters are written interlineally: e.g., fols. 3rb, 4va, 6rc, 23rb, 31vb, 33ra, 37va, 118vc.&#xD;
- Erasures in fol. 11va and corrections over erasures in fol. 9va.&#xD;
- Crude drawings in pencil in the bottom margin of fol. 109v.&#xD;
- Strip of textile is inserted in fol. 139, for navigating inthe text.</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
